00:33:35.620 --> 00:33:39.890
There's an NGO that went
into a village in Kenya.

00:33:39.890 --> 00:33:43.050
And the women were
walking like 5 miles

00:33:43.050 --> 00:33:46.020
to clean water every day.

00:33:46.020 --> 00:33:50.140
And so they came in and they
built a well in the village.

00:33:50.140 --> 00:33:52.830
And the women kept
walking the five miles.

00:33:52.830 --> 00:33:55.170
Well, no one
stopped to ask them,

00:33:55.170 --> 00:33:56.344
we're going to build a well.

00:33:56.344 --> 00:33:57.760
Where would you
like us to put it?

00:33:57.760 --> 00:34:00.440
So finally, after the fact,
cause they were still puzzled,

00:34:00.440 --> 00:34:02.530
they asked, why are you
still walking five miles?

00:34:02.530 --> 00:34:04.930
And they said, well, it's
to get away from the men.

00:34:04.930 --> 00:34:07.422
That's our time to get away.

00:34:07.422 --> 00:34:08.505
No one asked the question.

00:34:08.505 --> 00:34:10.629
So they were like, well,
what if we did it halfway?

00:34:10.629 --> 00:34:12.449
They're like, perfect.

00:34:12.449 --> 00:34:13.909
And that was the
well they went to.

00:34:13.909 --> 00:34:17.070
So we can't forget that
this data is great.

00:34:17.070 --> 00:34:19.270
But we're all human
beings, right?

00:34:19.270 --> 00:34:21.810
And there's aspects
to our behavior

00:34:21.810 --> 00:34:24.090
that can't be put
on a spreadsheet.

00:34:24.090 --> 00:34:28.139
So the emotion and the
high touch of a brand.

00:34:28.139 --> 00:34:32.889
